FBIS4-40318 "drsov116_g_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Vitebsk Council To Urge Referendum on Russian Language Vitebsk Council To Urge Referendum on Russian Language WS1606083194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 GMT 16 Jun 94 WS1606083194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Belarusian BFN [Text] A session of the Vitebsk City Council has resolved to address the Supreme Soviet with a request to consider the possibility of holding a nationwide referendum regarding the issue of granting official status to the Russian language in Belarus. The reason for such an appeal to the highest legislative body was a poll conducted among Vitebsk residents, which was held by an initiative group. The poll showed that 5,000 city residents support the idea of holding -- on the same day as presidential elections -- a city-wide referendum regarding the introduction of bilingualism. Such a stance is also supported [words indistinct] by 52 people's deputies in the Vitebsk City Council.
